PRIMARY SYSTEM COMPONENTS

QUANTITY	DESCRIPTION
4	Screw Compressor Packages
1	Evaporative Condenser
1	High-Pressure / Thermosiphon Receiver
1	High Temperature Recirculator with two ammonia pumps
1	Low Temperature Recirculator with two ammonia pumps
2	Oil Pots (one at each recirculator)
5	Evaporator Coil Units (10Â°F Shipping Dock)
4	Evaporator Coil Units (-20Â°F Freezer)
1	Auto Purger
1	Ammonia Diffusion Tank (18,000 gal. capacity)

Safety systems include:

1.	Pressure relief valves on all pressure vessels;
2.	Compressor safety cutouts and control panels to shut down the compressor operation if safe operating conditions are exceeded;
3.	Liquid level float switches;
4.	High level vessel alarms;
5.	Ventilation system for continuous and emergency ventilation;
6.	Emergency Control Station with emergency ventilation fan switch and emergency shutdown switches;
7.	Ammonia detection and alarm system for response to elevated levels of ammonia vapor.  Detection will trigger the emergency ventilation system, emergency shutdown, and audible/visual alarms at preset levels;
8.	Spring-loaded, self-closing oil drain valves;
9.	Manual stop valves;
10.	Manual and solenoid-controlled "King Valve" to stop liquid refrigerant flow from the high-pressure receiver;
11.	Physical barriers to protect equipment/piping from collisions (e.g. bollards);
12.	Fire dump box for fire department use only to relieve system overpressure;
13.	Fire sprinkler system;
14.	Fire extinguishers; and
15.	Emergency showers and eyewash stations

